member.name: T:Orc.Wizard.INavigationStrategy
member.summary: An INavigationStrategy object defines how forward and backward navigation occurs within the wizard when the user clicks the "Next" or the "Back" button. Providing a custom implementation of this interface allows to customize the default behaviour of moving forward/backward one page at a time.

member.name: M:Orc.Wizard.INavigationStrategy.GetIndexOfNextPage(Orc.Wizard.IWizard)
member.summary: Returns the index of the wizard page that should be displayed if the user clicks the "Next" button. Returns Orc.Wizard.WizardConfiguration.CannotNavigate to indicate that navigating forward is not possible.

member.name: M:Orc.Wizard.INavigationStrategy.GetIndexOfPreviousPage(Orc.Wizard.IWizard)
member.summary: Returns the index of the wizard page that should be displayed if the user clicks the "Back" button. Returns Orc.Wizard.WizardConfiguration.CannotNavigate to indicate that navigating backward is not possible.
